TITLE: Using Effects with Signals in Dart
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use effects with signals, showing how effects are triggered when signal values change and how to dispose of effects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rodydavis/signals.dart/blob/main/packages/signals/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
import 'package:signals/signals.dart';

final name = signal("Jane");
final surname = signal("Doe");
final fullName = computed(() => name.value + " " + surname.value);

// Logs: "Jane Doe"
effect(() => print(fullName.value));

// Updating one of its dependencies will automatically trigger
// the effect above, and will print "John Doe" to the console.
name.value = "John";

// Logs: "Jane Doe"
final dispose = effect(() => print(fullName.value));

// Destroy effect and subscriptions
dispose();

// Update does nothing, because no one is subscribed anymore.
// Even the computed `fullName` signal won't change, because it knows
// that no one listens to it.
surname.value = "Doe 2";
```

