TITLE: Auto-Disposing Signals in Dart
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create an auto-disposing signal that destroys itself when there are no more listeners. Includes checking if a signal is disposed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rodydavis/signals.dart/blob/main/website/src/content/docs/core/signal.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
final s = signal(0, autoDispose: true);
s.onDispose(() => print('Signal destroyed'));
final dispose = s.subscribe((_) {});
dispose();
final value = s.value; // 0
// prints: Signal destroyed

final s = signal(0);
print(s.disposed); // false
s.dispose();
print(s.disposed); // true
```

