TITLE: Demonstrating Minimal Updates with Signals in Dart
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how signals optimize computations by only computing values when they are read. It demonstrates that if a signal is never read, its dependencies are not computed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rodydavis/signals.dart/blob/main/website/src/content/docs/reference/overview.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
import 'package:signals/signals.dart';

final a = signal(0);
final b = computed(() => a.value + 1);
final c = computed(() => b.value + 1);
final d = computed(() => c.value + 1);

// if you never read `d` then none of the callbacks will be called

// All the callbacks will be called
print(d.value); // 3

// None of the callbacks will be called because the 
// value is cached at each node
print(d.value); // 3
```

