TITLE: Using untracked in Dart Effects
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use untracked to prevent subscriptions when reading signals in a callback within an effect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rodydavis/signals.dart/blob/main/packages/signals/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: dart
CODE:
```
final counter = signal(0);
final effectCount = signal(0);
final fn = () => effectCount.value + 1;

effect(() {
	print(counter.value);

	// Whenever this effect is triggered, run `fn` that gives new value
	effectCount.value = untracked(fn);
});
```

