TITLE: List Prepend Function Definition in CMake
DESCRIPTION: Helper function that prepends a prefix to each element in a list. Used as an alternative to list(TRANSFORM) for CMake 3.10 compatibility.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rodydavis/signals.dart/blob/main/examples/drift_example/linux/flutter/CMakeLists.txt#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cmake
CODE:
```
function(list_prepend LIST_NAME PREFIX)
    set(NEW_LIST "")
    foreach(element ${${LIST_NAME}})
        list(APPEND NEW_LIST "${PREFIX}${element}")
    endforeach(element)
    set(${LIST_NAME} "${NEW_LIST}" PARENT_SCOPE)
endfunction()
```

